"Hi @daritter, it's actually rather easy to deal with a so-far unknown decay model on the fly, see the section \"advanced usage\" I had at some point added to the README. This being said, it's just nicer to continue expanding the known models as they get created. But you folks at Belle have enhanced the master decay file with something new? OK, then we will need some info for the parser \u2026\r\n\r\nBTW, it would then be great to update your master decay file at `https://github.com/scikit-hep/decaylanguage/tree/master/decaylanguage/data` for the benefit of everyone.\n\nI've seen the README but that was still talking about a fixed list of models, now it seems people on my side started to use a dynamic list of models. And I'm quite sure it's actually not a new feature as we're stuck on a rather old evtgen for the time being so this is something which evtgen has supported for quite some time now :D\r\n\r\nAs a matter of fact looking in the `EvtGenBase/EvtDecayTable.cpp` there seem to be a few other things supported that decaylanguage doesn't do:\r\n\r\n* Define\r\n* ModelAlias\r\n* PythiaAliasParam\r\n* PythiaGenericParam\r\n* Particle\r\n* ChangeMassMin\r\n* ChangeMassMax\r\n* IncludeBirthFactor\r\n* IncludeDecayFactor\r\n* CopyDecay\r\n* RemoveDecay\r\n...\r\n\r\nAt least some of these are obviously a bad idea to have (Particle (re-)definition in the decay file seems like a recipe for unpleasantness to me) and I'm not demanding that you support all of that. But the ModelAlias actually sounds like a good idea. I've also seen the Change*Mass in one signal decay file of ours but there I'm more inclined on pushing this out of the decay file.\r\n\r\nDon't get me wrong, I'm really happy with the effort of decaylanguage. I am mostly making issues so that this is documented. Problem with giving you our decayfile always the same: we haven't managed to get our software licensed yet so I have to ... dance around that\n\nThanks very much @daritter for bringing this to our attention. I confess that I had not looked at that EvtGen file, being happily parsing LHCb decay files and the one we have from Belle right now in the repository. Clearly it would have been a good thing to do :D.\r\n\r\nNote that `Define` is actually supported since the beginning. But not the others on your list. I also noticed that EvtGen has `noPhotos` and `normalPhotos` as well as `yesPhotos`, and only the latter is known to `DecayLanguage`.\r\n\r\n> Don't get me wrong, I'm really happy with the effort of decaylanguage. I am mostly making issues so that this is documented. Problem with giving you our decayfile always the same: we haven't managed to get our software licensed yet so I have to ... dance around that\r\n\r\nI don't. It's *excellent* that you provide us with feedback and suggestions! That's super appreciated and I only regret that we get too little feedback - \"am happy\" is also welcome :-).\r\n\r\nIf software licensing is an issue you could maybe provide a few example lines related to the enhancements you need, as that should be enough to test code for the new functionality to support? Of course, if somebody commits a PR, even better!\n\nI just had a quick stab and supporting ModelAlias should not be too much work: If a ModelAlias is found then EvtGen stops parsing the decayline. So we can just have a `(model | LABEL)` in the lark parser and then verify that the label is actually in the alias list. There's still some weirdness on when evtgen wants or allows a semicolon I have to figure out\r\n\r\nI hope I find some time to work on this but to be honest I'm not sure how much time I will be able to spend\n\nHi @daritter, I hope you're doing well!\r\n\r\nListen, shall we try and get back to this issue/task? Let me re-state that \"If software licensing is an issue you could maybe provide a few example lines related to the enhancements you need, as that should be enough to test code for the new functionality to support? Of course, if somebody commits a PR, even better!\".\r\nThis is true for the required developments for introducing `ModelAlias` and the other missing keywords into the list of known keywords to the parser."